05:43.594 --> 05:45.130
See you with my own eyes.

05:45.262 --> 05:47.594
Where's Audrey?
Is she okay?

05:47.723 --> 05:49.509
All these months, I never dreamed
that you could actually be real,

05:49.642 --> 05:50.301
and then last night,

05:50.434 --> 05:52.049
l was watching the news,
and there you were,

05:52.186 --> 05:54.598
calling for Audrey Parker,
just like you did in my head.

05:54.730 --> 05:56.766
Um...

05:56.899 --> 05:59.390
Why don't we just, uh,
start with your name?

05:59.527 --> 06:00.858
Jennﬁeh

06:00.986 --> 06:02.362
Jennifer Mason.

06:02.821 --> 06:03.731
Yeah.

06:04.740 --> 06:07.527
Okay, six months ago,
l was working at the Boston Globe,

06:07.660 --> 06:10.197
actually having a pretty good day,
and then someone started shouting.

06:10.329 --> 06:12.320
So I got up from my cubicle
to see what was wrong,

06:12.456 --> 06:13.696
but there was no one there,

06:13.832 --> 06:15.368
but I could still hear the voices

06:15.501 --> 06:17.833
and all these names ——
Audrey, Howard, Nathan, Duke——

06:17.962 --> 06:21.045
and it wouldn't stop ——
the talking, the shouting, the crying.

06:21.173 --> 06:23.835
I could hear the same conversations
over and over,

06:23.968 --> 06:27.085
like a CD stuck on repeat,
so I thought I was going crazy.

06:27.221 --> 06:28.427
Well, it turns out l was.

06:28.556 --> 06:30.012
The doctors told me
l was schizophrenic.

06:30.140 --> 06:32.176
They told me
that the voices weren't real,

06:32.309 --> 06:34.220
that none of you...

06:35.813 --> 06:37.474
...were real.

06:43.779 --> 06:45.565
Your doctors were wrong.

06:45.698 --> 06:47.689
How is that possible?

06:47.825 --> 06:49.907
l have no idea.

06:50.035 --> 06:52.697
But look, you said it started
six months ago, right?

06:52.830 --> 06:54.195
—Yeah.
— I don't know how,

06:54.331 --> 06:58.119
but somehow I think
you were hearing my friends

06:58.252 --> 07:01.039
while we were stuck
in this, um, place.

07:01.171 --> 07:03.207
The barn?
That's what you called it.

07:03.340 --> 07:05.422
Yeah, the barn,
but it's not really a barn.

07:05.551 --> 07:06.757
I mean, it looks like a barn.

07:06.885 --> 07:10.924
Really, it's this, like,
big, crazy supernatural thing.

07:11.056 --> 07:12.887
No, no, no, no, Jennifer,
Jennifer, wait.

07:13.017 --> 07:15.884
| live in a town in Maine
called Haven.

07:16.020 --> 07:19.353
It's a place for people
who have special, um...

07:19.481 --> 07:21.096
abilities.

07:21.233 --> 07:22.814
We call them "troubled".

07:22.943 --> 07:24.399
Now, I think that's what you are

07:24.528 --> 07:27.065
and how you were able to hear
what you did.

07:27.197 --> 07:30.735
Okay, right now you're making me
feel more crazy, not less crazy.

07:30.868 --> 07:33.610
Yeah, I know how it sounds,

07:33.746 --> 07:35.452
but I'm telling you the truth.

07:35.581 --> 07:38.072
And if you somehow
are connected to the barn,

07:38.208 --> 07:39.243
then maybe
you can hear something

07:39.376 --> 07:41.583
that can help me
find my friend Audrey,

07:41.712 --> 07:44.624
'cause she must've fallen
out of the barn

07:44.757 --> 07:47.373
at the same time as me,
but I don't know where.

07:47.509 --> 07:50.637
After I was diagnosed,
I started taking medicine,

07:50.763 --> 07:53.721
and it made the voices stop,
and I haven't heard them since.

07:54.850 --> 07:57.466
That's okay. Look, we just need
to get you back to Haven.

07:57.603 --> 07:59.719
What? I'm not going anywhere
with you.

07:59.855 --> 08:02.267
ljust met you,
and you're some kind of criminal.

08:02.399 --> 08:05.891
Yes, lam a criminal,
but one with a heart of gold.

08:06.028 --> 08:07.984
Look, if you help me get out of here,

08:08.113 --> 08:09.614
we will figure out
what happened to you,

08:09.740 --> 08:12.732
and I bet you that Audrey can fix it.

08:13.744 --> 08:15.280
That's just what she does.

08:17.873 --> 08:19.704
