13:31.353 --> 13:34.766
Look, Nathan, I'm used
to people wanting me dead.

13:34.898 --> 13:36.684
What are you gonna do
about The Guard?

13:36.817 --> 13:38.182
l'll figure something out.
I need my resources.

13:38.318 --> 13:40.730
Got to send A.P.B.s out,
send hospitals descriptions.

13:40.862 --> 13:42.898
She could be hurt, disoriented.

13:43.740 --> 13:46.482
Okay, we got a full tank of gas
and some snacks for the drive.

13:46.618 --> 13:48.904
I don't know what you like,
but everyone likes Slim Jims.

13:50.080 --> 13:51.616
I like Slim Jims.

13:54.251 --> 13:56.287
Duke, you drive.
I need to talk to Jennifer.

13:56.420 --> 13:58.786
And you need to tell me
everything you know about the barn.

14:01.633 --> 14:04.124
This town's been through so much.

14:04.261 --> 14:06.217
How much more can people take?

14:06.346 --> 14:09.088
Well, the chief is doing
the best he can.

14:09.808 --> 14:11.298
Speak of the devil.

14:13.437 --> 14:14.973
Dwight.
Have they found anything——

14:15.105 --> 14:17.517
bomb materials,
trace of an accelerant?

14:18.316 --> 14:20.807
And hope still springs eternal.

14:21.570 --> 14:22.935
Nothing yet.

14:23.071 --> 14:26.108
Here we go again.
What do we blame this one on?

14:26.241 --> 14:27.230
It's a gas leak.

14:27.367 --> 14:29.153
A gas leak? Another one?

14:29.286 --> 14:31.151
Yeah, another one.

14:32.831 --> 14:34.822
You're not helping.

14:34.958 --> 14:36.243
I'm not the kind of help you need.

14:36.376 --> 14:38.367
That kind of help
was driven out of town.

14:38.503 --> 14:40.459
Or killed when the barn exploded.

14:41.089 --> 14:42.670
Duke called me this morning.

14:42.799 --> 14:45.461
Duke's alive?
Why didn't you tell me?

14:45.594 --> 14:46.458
ljust did.

14:47.429 --> 14:49.670
—[ Sighs]
—Are you two done?

14:49.806 --> 14:51.342
BOTH: Sorry, chief.

14:51.475 --> 14:54.387
[Cell phone ringing]

14:54.519 --> 14:56.020
What's up?

14:57.606 --> 14:58.595
I'll be right there.

14:58.732 --> 15:02.145
Somebody down at the beach
is frozen in glass.

15:02.277 --> 15:06.441
If this bomb is a trouble,
it's not the only one we got today.

15:08.033 --> 15:11.525
Okay, I got to get today's till
to the bank before it closes.

15:11.661 --> 15:13.322
You gonna be okay by yourself?

15:13.455 --> 15:14.535
Yeah, I think I got the hang of it.

15:14.664 --> 15:16.996
Did since the moment
you came in —— you're a natural.

15:17.125 --> 15:18.331
Well, I like it here.

15:18.460 --> 15:20.746
It's much better
than my last gig —— boring.

15:20.879 --> 15:22.289
Yeah, this place
will keep you hopping.

15:22.422 --> 15:24.504
At least most of the regulars
behave themselves.

15:24.633 --> 15:26.965
Tell that to the pinch bruises
on my ass.

15:27.094 --> 15:27.549
Oh, I don't know.

15:27.677 --> 15:30.134
You're pretty good at keeping
the bad boys in their place.

15:30.263 --> 15:33.050
Just looking for one guy,
you know, one decent guy.

15:33.183 --> 15:34.673
Is that too much to ask?

15:34.810 --> 15:37.677
You are wasting your time
looking around here.

15:38.688 --> 15:40.815
[Sighs]

15:59.960 --> 16:02.372
Hey, can I help you?

16:02.504 --> 16:06.873
Please.
Uh, can I get a local beer?

16:07.008 --> 16:08.748
What, like, a microbrew?

16:08.885 --> 16:13.219
Yeah, there's a good one, actually.
I think it's from Maine.

16:13.348 --> 16:15.964
[Laughs]
I can do better than that.

16:16.101 --> 16:17.466
Okay.

16:17.602 --> 16:19.012
Here.

16:26.236 --> 16:28.568
Oh, what a pretty little town.

16:29.030 --> 16:31.066
It has its moments.

16:31.199 --> 16:32.109
[Tires screech ]

16:38.248 --> 16:39.033
[Guns cock]

16:39.166 --> 16:41.282
Usually moments like this.

16:41.418 --> 16:43.329
Hello, Nathan.

16:43.461 --> 16:45.793
Get out of the car.

16:51.887 --> 16:54.424
Great, she's alive.

17:01.771 --> 17:04.057
Who's that woman?

17:04.191 --> 17:05.306
Jordan McKee.

17:05.442 --> 17:07.148
Her and Nathan used
to have a thing,

17:07.277 --> 17:08.608
but then he dumped her,
and I shot her,

17:08.737 --> 17:09.977
and the whole thing got weird.

17:10.113 --> 17:11.614
Oh.

17:16.620 --> 17:18.281
Way to keep a secret, Dave.

17:18.413 --> 17:20.825
Believe me,
you're glad we're here.

17:20.957 --> 17:22.948
Oh, yeah,
it's going splendidly so far.

17:23.084 --> 17:25.917
Jordan, put the gun down.

17:26.755 --> 17:28.746
Jordan, don't forget it was Nathan

17:28.882 --> 17:30.998
who found you unconscious
in that field.

17:31.134 --> 17:32.999
He explained your condition
to the doctor

17:33.136 --> 17:35.092
so he could operate on you.

17:35.222 --> 17:38.510
He could've let you die,
but he didn't.

17:38.642 --> 17:40.132
Maybe he should've.

17:41.269 --> 17:42.645
That gun goes off,

17:43.813 --> 17:46.350
the only person that dies here
today is me.

17:46.483 --> 17:48.019
What does he mean?

17:48.151 --> 17:50.437
Well, you see,
Dwight here's a bullet magnet.

17:50.570 --> 17:51.855
That's his trouble.

17:51.988 --> 17:53.524
Jordan fires that gun anywhere,

17:53.657 --> 17:55.443
the only person
it's gonna hit is Dwight.

17:55.575 --> 17:56.815
Oh.

17:57.869 --> 17:59.825
Is that what you want?

18:04.876 --> 18:06.832
No.

18:08.838 --> 18:10.499
But he has to pay.

18:10.632 --> 18:11.963
He will.

18:13.134 --> 18:14.169
Duke.

18:15.136 --> 18:16.512
Sasquatch.

18:16.638 --> 18:21.758
You told us Duke was in the barn
with Audrey when it was destroyed.

18:21.893 --> 18:23.349
He was...

18:23.478 --> 18:26.515
which means Audrey is still alive.

18:26.648 --> 18:28.184
Oh, whoa, whoa, what?

18:28.316 --> 18:29.396
[lndistinct chatter]

18:29.526 --> 18:30.857
Quiet!

18:32.070 --> 18:33.185
Where is she?

18:34.364 --> 18:36.696
That's why I came back...

18:36.825 --> 18:38.907
to find her.

18:39.035 --> 18:41.492
Audrey and l
are gonna end the troubles.

18:41.621 --> 18:42.906
Audrey going into that barn ——

18:43.039 --> 18:44.745
that's what should've ended
the troubles.

18:44.874 --> 18:46.580
There's another way.

18:49.296 --> 18:50.706
This is Jennifer.

18:50.839 --> 18:53.046
She's troubled,
connected to the barn somehow.

18:53.174 --> 18:55.756
She heard Audrey and Howard
talking.

19:01.308 --> 19:04.050
Howard told Audrey
that there was another way

19:04.185 --> 19:06.221
she could end the troubles,

19:06.354 --> 19:10.347
but not just for 27 years,
but forever.

19:10.483 --> 19:11.563
How?

19:11.985 --> 19:15.022
By killing the person
she loves the most.

19:15.155 --> 19:16.941
By killing me.

19:17.073 --> 19:18.859
Is this some sick joke?

19:18.992 --> 19:20.072
Nathan's telling the truth.

19:20.201 --> 19:23.034
That's exactly what Arla told me
when Vince and I had her prisoner.

19:23.163 --> 19:26.530
So you could kill me, Jordan,
get your revenge,

19:26.666 --> 19:28.577
get to live the rest of your life
troubled.

19:28.710 --> 19:31.201
Last touch you ever feel
will have been mine.

19:33.089 --> 19:35.296
Or you can let me live.

19:35.425 --> 19:36.790
|wi|| find Audrey.

19:36.926 --> 19:39.212
l'll convince her to kill me.

19:39.929 --> 19:41.635
The troubles will end forever.

19:41.765 --> 19:43.801
And you expect us to believe that?

19:43.933 --> 19:47.801
Hey, crazy town, you know him.
You all do.

19:47.937 --> 19:50.974
All he's ever wanted to do
was protect Haven,

19:51.107 --> 19:53.098
and he's willing to give his life
to do that.

19:54.235 --> 19:56.271
That's the craziest thing
I ever heard.

19:56.404 --> 19:58.315
Crazier than anything else
that's been going on around here?

19:58.448 --> 20:00.564
And Nathan is saying
he can end all that,

20:00.700 --> 20:03.783
and he's willing to give his life
to do it.

20:05.789 --> 20:08.246
What do you all have to lose
by letting him try?

20:20.845 --> 20:23.461
What the hell is that?

20:24.140 --> 20:25.004
Take cover!

20:25.141 --> 20:26.472
Everybody, take cover!

20:26.601 --> 20:30.093
[Overlapping shouting]

20:31.106 --> 20:33.472
What is that?
Oh, my God.

20:47.163 --> 20:49.745
I don't like it here!

20:59.634 --> 21:02.842
If this thing crashes down,
we're dead!

21:31.124 --> 21:32.705
What was that?

21:32.834 --> 21:34.745
Welcome home.

21:34.878 --> 21:37.415
There was a tornado right here.
Where did it go?

21:37.547 --> 21:39.162
No way that was a normal tornado.

21:39.299 --> 21:41.460
This been happening a lot?

21:41.593 --> 21:43.424
No, no.
This is something new.

21:43.553 --> 21:46.295
Okay, you guys, take Nathan
and Crocker to the safe house

21:46.431 --> 21:47.216
and sit on them.

21:47.348 --> 21:48.724
[Gun cocks]

21:48.850 --> 21:50.681
No, no, hold up, hold up.

21:50.810 --> 21:52.926
Listen, you saw what happened
at the bookstore this morning,

21:53.062 --> 21:55.053
and I found another body
down at the beach.

21:55.190 --> 21:58.102
And whatever that was,
I need their help.

21:58.234 --> 22:00.611
I agree.

22:00.737 --> 22:03.900
No, I'm not here
to fight the troubles.

22:04.032 --> 22:05.112
You want me to convince The Guard

22:05.241 --> 22:09.280
you'll do anything to save Haven,
even die?

22:09.412 --> 22:10.948
Well, maybe start smaller.

22:11.080 --> 22:13.537
Maybe start now.

22:14.542 --> 22:15.952
Fine.

22:16.085 --> 22:19.498
I'll do what I can,
but I am here to find Audrey.

22:20.381 --> 22:22.121
All right,
we need to spread out.

22:22.258 --> 22:26.376
Check the surrounding blocks.
We may have casualties.

22:29.641 --> 22:31.427
Move!

22:36.105 --> 22:37.311
You should come back
to the police station.

22:37.440 --> 22:38.805
I'll show you what I've got so far.

22:38.942 --> 22:41.149
Oh, me. I want to go
to the police station.

22:41.736 --> 22:44.102
Police stations are safe, right?

22:45.740 --> 22:46.855
Usually.

22:48.743 --> 22:51.075
Hey.

22:51.996 --> 22:54.612
Okay, show's over.

22:54.749 --> 22:56.831
Your plan isn't really
to let Audrey kill you.

22:56.960 --> 23:00.452
I mean, you were just putting one
over on The Guard, right?

23:00.588 --> 23:02.169
No, that's the plan.

23:02.298 --> 23:05.381
I'm not really up on what's going on,
but that is a bad plan.

23:05.510 --> 23:07.751
It's the only way
to stop the troubles.

23:07.887 --> 23:10.344
Everything that's happening
in this town is my fault.

23:10.473 --> 23:12.179
Audrey's never gonna go for this.

23:12.308 --> 23:14.173
Audrey was willing
to walk into that barn

23:14.310 --> 23:16.562
and have her personality
stripped away,

23:16.688 --> 23:18.644
to forget everyone
she ever cared about.

23:18.773 --> 23:21.435
Audrey was willing to die
to stop the troubles.

23:21.568 --> 23:23.900
Let's just say you're right.

23:24.028 --> 23:28.988
That means for the troubles to end,
you have to be Audrey's true love.

23:30.493 --> 23:32.324
Are you sure about that?

23:32.453 --> 23:36.742
I've never been more sure
about anything in my entire life.

23:42.547 --> 23:44.378
So I haven't seen you
around here before.

23:44.507 --> 23:46.213
I haven't come in before.

23:46.342 --> 23:47.923
Never had a reason...

23:48.052 --> 23:49.212
till now.

23:50.847 --> 23:53.429
Name's, uh, William.

23:54.475 --> 23:55.681
Lexie.

23:55.810 --> 23:59.177
Lexie?
Pretty name.

23:59.731 --> 24:00.891
You worked here long?

24:01.024 --> 24:02.685
—Mm, about a month.
—Hmm.

24:02.817 --> 24:04.227
Never worked in a bar before.

24:04.360 --> 24:05.896
You know, ljust thought
it would be fun.

24:06.029 --> 24:07.940
Thought I'd meet
some interesting people.

24:11.242 --> 24:13.904
Are you interesting, William?

24:14.495 --> 24:15.621
I've been told.

24:15.747 --> 24:19.365
Some things I like
to find out for myself.

24:22.295 --> 24:26.334
Well...l'm not sure
this is the place.

24:26.466 --> 24:29.629
My shift ends in a few hours.

24:30.720 --> 24:32.836
I think I know someplace we can go.

24:36.726 --> 24:37.590
[Door closes]

24:37.727 --> 24:40.059
[Ominous music]

24:45.276 --> 24:46.561
Do you know that guy?

24:48.696 --> 24:49.731
No.

24:53.618 --> 24:54.949
He has a gun.

24:55.078 --> 24:57.444
Yeah, could tell
by the way he moved.

24:57.580 --> 25:01.323
Wow. Wait.
Are you a cop or something?

25:01.459 --> 25:02.949
Not even a little.

25:03.086 --> 25:04.622
Damn, I hope
he doesn't try something.

25:04.754 --> 25:06.085
The last time I tried
to call the cops,

25:06.214 --> 25:08.170
it took them, like,
45 minutes to get here.

25:08.299 --> 25:09.914
Looks like you'll have to handle it
on your own.

25:10.051 --> 25:11.006
[ Scoffs ]

25:11.135 --> 25:13.592
Are you kidding?

25:15.139 --> 25:17.630
Oh, my God, he wants me
to go over there.

25:17.767 --> 25:20.474
—Can I get some quarters?
—Really?

25:20.603 --> 25:22.013
For the jukebox.

25:25.900 --> 25:28.562
Unbelievable.

25:28.695 --> 25:31.027
Thanks.

25:46.587 --> 25:48.418
Hi, what can I get you?

25:48.923 --> 25:50.379
Have a seat.

25:50.967 --> 25:54.050
You know, I'd —— I'd love to,
but we're really busy right now, so...

25:54.178 --> 25:56.965
Sit down.

26:19.954 --> 26:21.865
Listen, the cashbox
already went to the bank, okay?

26:21.998 --> 26:24.205
We don't have anything here,
just a couple bucks for change.

26:24.333 --> 26:27.825
I don't want your money.

26:29.297 --> 26:31.379
Well, then, what do you want?

27:01.579 --> 27:03.661
Hey, are you okay?

27:03.790 --> 27:06.202
Yeah. I think so.

27:07.168 --> 27:08.203
You gonna be all right?

27:09.045 --> 27:11.206
I'm good. I'm good.

27:17.762 --> 27:19.468
??? a police chief, huh?

27:19.597 --> 27:20.882
Yeah, Teagues talked me into it.

27:21.015 --> 27:23.301
We couldn't risk an outsider
coming in, poking around.

27:23.434 --> 27:25.811
Besides, town needed
a familiar face.

27:25.937 --> 27:26.767
When you disappeared,

27:26.896 --> 27:28.887
people that don't know
about the troubles didn't know why.

27:29.023 --> 27:30.263
A lot of them took it hard.

27:30.399 --> 27:31.730
And the people who knew why?

27:31.859 --> 27:33.645
The ones who knew what you did
took it even harder.

27:33.778 --> 27:35.484
You're taking a big gamble
coming back, Nate.

27:35.613 --> 27:36.728
Hold on. Wait.

27:36.864 --> 27:40.152
Is that Nathan Wuornos,
the old chief?

27:40.284 --> 27:42.275
I knew he wouldn't stay away.

27:44.163 --> 27:45.824
One of our latest incidents.

27:45.957 --> 27:49.165
Anywhere else but Haven,
I'd say it was a bombing.

27:49.293 --> 27:52.080
It wasn't a bomb. There was
no particulates found at the scene.

27:52.213 --> 27:54.454
Witnesses said it was like being
in the middle of a windstorm,

27:54.590 --> 27:56.296
only there was no wind outside.

27:56.425 --> 27:58.507
The wind just appeared
like the tornado?

27:58.636 --> 28:00.251
What could do that?

28:04.267 --> 28:05.723
We found that this afternoon.

28:05.852 --> 28:08.810
Lucassi said the sand got so hot
that it turned to glass

28:08.938 --> 28:10.144
and the victim was trapped inside.

28:10.273 --> 28:12.264
This was here in Haven?

28:12.400 --> 28:13.936
You know what it is?

28:14.068 --> 28:15.353
Yeah, it's called a fulgurite.

28:15.486 --> 28:19.354
l was on a beach in the Congo once.
These things were everywhere.

28:19.490 --> 28:22.277
The natives —— they called them
"petrified lightning."

28:22.410 --> 28:23.616
Lightning?

28:23.744 --> 28:26.076
The bolts would super—heat the sand.

28:26.205 --> 28:27.411
These things were
all over the place,

28:27.540 --> 28:30.657
except the ones I saw didn't have
dead bodies inside of them.

28:30.793 --> 28:33.830
Autopsy said the victim died
within the last 48 hours.

28:33.963 --> 28:36.295
We haven't had a lightning storm
here for weeks.

28:36.424 --> 28:40.087
So from out of nowhere,
we got wind, lightning, tornados ——

28:40.219 --> 28:42.005
all forms of extreme weather.

28:42.138 --> 28:43.423
So we got a bunch of people
running around

28:43.556 --> 28:44.796
who can control the weather.

28:46.100 --> 28:48.432
Or maybe just one person...

28:48.561 --> 28:50.097
Marion Caldwell.

28:50.229 --> 28:52.140
I didn't read anything about her
in the files.

28:52.273 --> 28:54.980
That's because there was never
an official report.

28:55.109 --> 28:57.521
It was Audrey's first day in Haven.

28:57.653 --> 29:01.145
Audrey discovered Marion
had a weather trouble,

29:01.282 --> 29:02.488
killed someone,

29:02.617 --> 29:05.984
but we thought her trouble
was under control.

29:06.120 --> 29:08.202
—|'|| get an address.
—Yeah.

29:10.041 --> 29:11.997
Remember the marina we passed
on the way here?

29:12.126 --> 29:13.286
—Mm—hmm.
—I want you to go there.

29:13.419 --> 29:14.044
That's where my boat is.

29:14.170 --> 29:16.536
The harbor master will show you
which one is mine.

29:16.672 --> 29:18.754
—You'll be safe there.
—|s there anything to eat there?

29:18.883 --> 29:21.124
'Cause l have to take my meds,
and l have to take them with food.

29:21.260 --> 29:23.125
Um, the gull.

29:23.262 --> 29:25.548
It'll be closed, but the food
in the freezer is still good.

29:25.681 --> 29:26.591
I'm gonna get, uh ——

29:26.724 --> 29:28.464
Stan.

29:29.268 --> 29:30.508
—Him. See him?
—I see him.

29:30.645 --> 29:32.431
He'll take you there.
You can trust him.

29:32.563 --> 29:33.598
Got an address.

29:33.731 --> 29:35.096
Vince and Dave will meet us there.

29:35.232 --> 29:36.608
Let's go.

29:36.734 --> 29:38.395
It'll be okay.

29:47.370 --> 29:49.986
I know you're not happy
about my deal with Nathan.

29:50.122 --> 29:52.158
And not just me.

29:52.291 --> 29:53.952
I'm hearing a lot of rumbling.

29:54.085 --> 29:56.246
The Guard know you never really
wanted Nathan dead,

29:56.379 --> 29:57.243
even after what he did.

29:57.380 --> 29:58.961
It makes you look weak.

30:01.300 --> 30:03.256
I think you know better.

30:03.386 --> 30:05.047
And you know
I'll do whatever it takes

30:05.179 --> 30:08.592
to keep this town together,
to end the troubles.

30:08.724 --> 30:11.010
So will I.

30:12.478 --> 30:13.718
This isn't about Nathan.

30:13.854 --> 30:15.810
This is about Audrey,
and you know it.

30:15.940 --> 30:20.479
All you're thinking is that
she's alive and she's coming back.

30:22.321 --> 30:26.155
I met her decades ago.
Her name was Sarah.

30:26.283 --> 30:29.150
She helped the town then, too.

30:29.870 --> 30:32.077
And you're still carrying a torch.

30:32.748 --> 30:35.330
You, Nathan, Duke.

30:35.459 --> 30:38.246
Really don't get the appeal.

30:41.298 --> 30:43.584
Go home, Jordan.

30:45.720 --> 30:47.176
Yeah.

30:51.142 --> 30:54.259
[Wind gusting]

30:54.395 --> 30:57.979
I'm not a meteorologist,
but this doesn't look good.

30:58.107 --> 31:00.814
Marion's in there.

31:05.614 --> 31:08.105
Marion?

31:08.242 --> 31:10.073
Hello?

31:12.788 --> 31:16.326
It's got to be 20 below zero in here.

31:16.459 --> 31:19.792
How did, um, Audrey talk Marion
down the first time?

31:19.920 --> 31:23.458
She showed Marion that her friend,
Conrad, secretly loved her,

31:23.591 --> 31:26.424
that they could be happy together.

31:27.720 --> 31:29.585
Damn it.

31:29.722 --> 31:31.678
You guys should get out of here
before you freeze to death.

31:31.807 --> 31:33.388
Audrey's the immune one.

31:33.517 --> 31:36.350
This cold is affecting you
just as much as it us.

31:36.479 --> 31:40.142
Yeah, but I can't feel it.
I'll last longer.

31:40.274 --> 31:41.309
Go.

31:44.403 --> 31:46.940
—Go.
—Five minutes.

31:47.073 --> 31:49.860
Then we're coming back.

31:53.079 --> 31:55.195
Goddamn it!

32:27.238 --> 32:30.401
Nathan Wuornos...

32:32.243 --> 32:36.156
You came back.

32:36.288 --> 32:38.324
Marion...

32:41.043 --> 32:42.283
What happened?

32:42.419 --> 32:44.910
My trouble...

32:45.047 --> 32:48.005
It came back, too...

32:49.552 --> 32:52.840
...because of you.

32:52.972 --> 32:54.303
[lce cracking]

33:19.957 --> 33:25.168
Troubles were supposed to go away
when Audrey left.

33:25.296 --> 33:27.878
That's what everyone said.

33:28.007 --> 33:29.838
I know.

33:29.967 --> 33:32.629
And you can take it out on me,

33:32.761 --> 33:35.423
but you have to stop hurting
innocent people.

33:36.223 --> 33:37.929
What people?

33:38.058 --> 33:39.923
Don't you know what you're doing?

33:41.187 --> 33:44.600
You've been creating
windstorms, cyclones,

33:44.732 --> 33:47.064
lightning strikes all over town.

33:53.282 --> 33:54.237
[Grunts]

34:04.668 --> 34:06.829
Marion, did you see her?

34:06.962 --> 34:09.078
No, as a matter of fact,
we haven't.

34:09.215 --> 34:11.831
But have a look around.
I'm pretty sure she's in there.

34:11.967 --> 34:13.468
This storm's getting worse.

34:13.594 --> 34:16.006
And it's blowing straight
towards the center of town.

34:21.018 --> 34:23.680
I didn't know.

34:23.812 --> 34:26.064
What happened?

34:26.190 --> 34:28.522
Why did your trouble come back?

34:40.120 --> 34:41.735
Conrad?

34:46.710 --> 34:50.749
Two days ago,
he was working on the porch,

34:50.881 --> 34:54.840
fixing the damage
from the meteor storm.

34:55.803 --> 35:00.342
He came inside and said
that his arm had gone numb.

35:02.142 --> 35:04.224
Then he collapsed.

35:04.353 --> 35:05.934
Heart attack?

35:06.063 --> 35:10.147
He had one
a couple of months ago, but...

35:10.276 --> 35:12.892
this one was worse.

35:13.028 --> 35:15.690
He stopped breathing.

35:16.573 --> 35:17.824
He...

35:17.950 --> 35:21.568
Died, and your trouble came back.

35:21.704 --> 35:26.744
But what if I could've taken him
to the hospital, or I could've ——

35:26.875 --> 35:29.412
No, he was gone.

35:29.545 --> 35:31.376
There was nothing you could do.

35:31.505 --> 35:32.369
[Whimpers]

35:32.506 --> 35:34.417
There's something
you have to do now, Marion.

35:34.550 --> 35:36.541
You have to stop this.

35:38.429 --> 35:40.260
You have to let Conrad go.

35:40.389 --> 35:44.098
[Moaning]

35:44.226 --> 35:47.764
[Thunder booming,
wind gusting]

35:47.896 --> 35:49.761
[Lightning cracks]

35:49.898 --> 35:50.933
Oh!

35:55.404 --> 35:56.644
No!

35:56.780 --> 35:59.613
No, no!

35:59.742 --> 36:00.822
[Sobbing]
No!

36:12.546 --> 36:14.878
I'm sorry, Marion.

36:15.007 --> 36:16.747
I know how hard it is.

36:16.884 --> 36:19.466
No, you don't.

36:19.595 --> 36:21.961
Yes, I do.

36:22.097 --> 36:25.134
The troubles are still here
because of me.

36:25.267 --> 36:29.931
Because I couldn't accept
that Audrey had to go away.

36:30.689 --> 36:32.725
Because I couldn't bare to lose her.

36:32.858 --> 36:34.598
Because”.

36:35.569 --> 36:38.026
Because I couldn't let go,

36:38.155 --> 36:40.988
so many people were hurt.

36:41.658 --> 36:43.569
People like you.

36:46.288 --> 36:49.030
Then why did you come back?

37:02.638 --> 37:06.051
Because I got a second chance
to make it right.

37:06.850 --> 37:10.638
I won't let more people be hurt
because of me.

37:12.272 --> 37:13.478
And Conrad ——

37:13.607 --> 37:18.067
He wouldn't want you
hurting people because of him.

37:18.195 --> 37:20.982
I don't think
that I can live without him.

37:21.115 --> 37:22.821
[Crying]

37:25.160 --> 37:29.574
I loved him so much.

37:36.630 --> 37:39.087
What you're doing, this ——

37:39.216 --> 37:42.003
this isn't love.

37:44.680 --> 37:47.012
[Sobbing]

38:24.511 --> 38:25.921
It's all over now.

38:34.521 --> 38:36.261
Whatever you did,
it must have worked.

38:37.149 --> 38:39.731
I learned from the best.

38:41.528 --> 38:43.564
Marion didn't want
to hurt anyone.

38:43.697 --> 38:45.904
Yeah, well, they never do.

38:46.033 --> 38:48.365
Eh, some of them do.

38:50.245 --> 38:52.201
Thank you.

38:55.501 --> 38:57.617
The town will never
accept you back as chief,

38:57.753 --> 39:00.244
not the way you left things,

39:00.380 --> 39:03.167
but I convinced The Guard
that I need you on the force

39:03.300 --> 39:05.632
and that it's the best way
for me to keep my eye on you.

39:06.386 --> 39:07.466
Don't want it.

39:07.596 --> 39:09.257
Nathan, look what happened today.

39:09.389 --> 39:11.380
I've been trying to hold
this place together for six months,

39:11.517 --> 39:13.633
and I can't do it anymore.

39:13.769 --> 39:17.512
When the troubles didn't go away,
people lost hope.

39:17.648 --> 39:18.979
We need you.

39:19.107 --> 39:22.190
l have to find Audrey.

39:22.319 --> 39:26.483
You did say that access
to police resources

39:26.615 --> 39:28.321
was the only reason
you came back.

39:28.450 --> 39:32.614
If you were just a detective,
you'd be under less scrutiny.

39:32.746 --> 39:36.409
Maybe bending the rules
here and there might be easier.

39:41.421 --> 39:44.003
I'll do what I can,

39:44.132 --> 39:47.670
but it's all just a Band—Aid
until we find Audrey.

40:18.792 --> 40:21.875
Hey! There you are.

40:22.004 --> 40:23.369
Yep.

40:23.505 --> 40:25.006
Did you find the tornado lady?

40:25.132 --> 40:27.498
Yeah, as a matter of fact, we did.

40:27.634 --> 40:29.750
Okay, this place should be closed.

40:29.886 --> 40:32.093
Oh, I'm glad it wasn't.
I was starving.

40:32.222 --> 40:33.928
And this is
the world's best margarita.

40:34.057 --> 40:35.843
Totally worth the cheat.

40:37.019 --> 40:37.758
You don't drink?

40:37.894 --> 40:39.225
Well, I'm not supposed to
on my meds,

40:39.354 --> 40:42.221
but your brother and I decided
that this is worth the exception.

40:42.357 --> 40:43.563
My who?

40:43.692 --> 40:45.023
Your brother.

40:45.819 --> 40:48.026
Duke?

40:49.656 --> 40:50.691
Wade?

40:50.824 --> 40:52.610
You're alive.

40:53.702 --> 40:56.785
So cool that your brother owns a bar.

40:56.913 --> 41:01.623
Yeah, super cool.

41:09.092 --> 41:10.298
Thank you.

41:10.427 --> 41:12.634
I don't know what I would've done
if you hadn't been here.

41:12.763 --> 41:13.923
You'd have been fine.

41:14.056 --> 41:16.638
Are you kidding me?
That guy had a gun.

41:16.767 --> 41:19.304
I don't think I've actually been
that close to one in person before.

41:19.436 --> 41:21.267
[Chuckles]

41:21.396 --> 41:22.806
Yeah, you have.

41:22.939 --> 41:24.600
Lexie, l have a confession.

41:24.733 --> 41:26.269
That guy was here because of me.

41:26.401 --> 41:28.392
What? Why?

41:28.528 --> 41:34.990
He was afraid I was gonna
tell you something,

41:35.118 --> 41:38.360
a secret.

41:39.206 --> 41:40.161
A secret?

41:40.290 --> 41:41.621
—About you.
—About me?

41:41.750 --> 41:44.617
How —— how could you tell me
any secrets? We've just met.

41:48.215 --> 41:49.580
Like what?

41:49.716 --> 41:51.377
Like...

41:54.346 --> 41:57.088
You think your name's Lexie,

41:57.224 --> 41:58.680
but it's not.

42:00.394 --> 42:05.184
In fact,
you're someone else entirely.

42:06.900 --> 42:08.561
Congratulations.

42:08.694 --> 42:12.027
You just won the prize
for the creepiest pick—up line ever.

42:12.155 --> 42:13.895
It's not a line, it's the truth.

42:14.032 --> 42:16.819
And unless you let me help you
find out who you are...

42:17.828 --> 42:19.489
Then what?

42:21.123 --> 42:22.579
No, what's gonna happen?

42:22.958 --> 42:25.950
A lot of people are gonna die.
